rlm-pubsub-open

Browse Pub/Sub topics across one or more GCP projects via fzf and
open the selected topic in the GCP console.

Projects are read from the environment variable PUBSUB_OPEN_PROJECTS,
which must be set before calling this function:

  export PUBSUB_OPEN_PROJECTS=my-project-prod:my-project-dev

PUBSUB_OPEN_PROJECTS is a colon-separated list of GCP project IDs.
Each entry is shown as "project/topic-name".

CACHING
  The topic list is cached in ~/.cache/pubsub-open/ keyed by the
  sorted project list. On the first run the list is fetched from
  GCP; subsequent runs load instantly from the cache.

  The fzf header shows how old the cache is. To refresh it, select
  the "--- REFRESH CACHE ---" entry at the top of the list; this
  deletes the cache file and re-fetches all topics before re-opening
  the picker.

On selection the function:
  1. Prints the GCP console URL to stdout.
  2. Copies the URL to the clipboard (pbcopy on macOS,
     xclip/xsel on Linux).
  3. Opens the URL in the system browser (open on macOS,
     xdg-open on Linux).

The fzf preview pane shows the topic details via
"gcloud pubsub topics describe".

Requires: gcloud (Google Cloud SDK), fzf.
